            <div class="sub_stand_out">
                <h3 class="small_heading"> II. 1. Program origin </h3>
                <p class="description"> 
                    In a globalized economy, the emergence of specialized sectors has allowed a distinct separation of the company's activities. As information and
                    knowledge are increasingly specialized and fragmented, their production is an activity separate from the other activities of the company. The
                    knowledge management thus focuses on the production of knowledge for competitiveness.
                    To control information, companies must use the information cycle, which is established in three steps: collection of raw information by carrying
                    out monitoring and collection work, then, create knowledge from this information using intelligent software and human intelligence, and finally,
                    use this knowledge in the form of strategic information, this cycle can only be conducted through business intelligence work.
                    The Bachelor in Business Intelligence and Knowledge Management is a course program that spans one year and is aimed at holders of a degree
                    in science, economics, management and information science of Associates level. The course is organized in two semesters each with teaching in
                    the form of lectures, tutorials and practical work. Part of the second semester is devoted exclusively to a professional internship.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="sub_stand_out">
